updated, although there's some more references to `GAZEBO_DEPRECATED(1.10)` that came from other merges:

~~~
gazebo/sensors/Sensor.hh:              GAZEBO_DEPRECATED(1.10);
gazebo/sensors/SensorsIface.hh:        const std::string &_parentName) GAZEBO_DEPRECATED(1.10);
gazebo/sensors/SensorManager.hh:                  const std::string &_parentName) GAZEBO_DEPRECATED(1.10);
gazebo/common/Plugin.hh:              gzerr << "LTDL is deprecated as of Gazebo 1.10\n";
gazebo/physics/Collision.hh:      public: void SetContactsEnabled(bool _enable) GAZEBO_DEPRECATED(1.10);
gazebo/physics/Collision.hh:      public: bool GetContactsEnabled() const GAZEBO_DEPRECATED(1.10);
gazebo/physics/Collision.hh:      public: void AddContact(const Contact &_contact) GAZEBO_DEPRECATED(1.10);
gazebo/rendering/Scene.hh:                  const std::string &_newName) GAZEBO_DEPRECATED(1.10);
~~~

Should we go ahead and replace them all?

it's more readable as:
~~~
  this->dampingCoefficient[0] = 0;
  this->dampingCoefficient[1] = 0;
  this->stiffnessCoefficient[0] = 0;
  this->stiffnessCoefficient[1] = 0;
~~~
